To include a blog on your site, add the following lines to your _init.js file:


core.blog.urls();
core.core.routes();

allowModule = { blog: {} }; // adds the blog to your Applications section in Admin
routes = new Routes();
routes.setDefault( "index.jxp" );



Then add the following to your main file (index.jxp, in this case):

<%

core.blog.urls();

head.addCSS("/~~/blog/assets/blog_post.css");
core.blog.urls();

var result = Blog.handleRequest( request );

if ( result.posts.length == 1 ){
    if(request && request.addComment == "yes") {
        Blog.handlePosts(request, result.posts[0], user);
    }
    core.blog.pieces.post({post: result.posts[0], user: user, comments_enabled: result.posts[0].commentsEnabled});
}
else if (result.posts.length > 1) {
    core.blog.pieces.postSnippetList({posts: result.posts});
}
else {
    %>
    No posts!
    <%
}

%>


For customization options, look at the comments at the beginning of corejs/blog/pieces/post.djang10.  Each included template piece is in its own div so that parts of the page can easily be re-rendered asynchronously.
